author: James Dator
title: David Ross' 'Dancing With the Stars' debut was full of baseball and sassy butt bumps
text:
David Ross made his debut on Dancing With the Stars on Monday night and the former Cubs’ catcher ensured his routine was as baseball-packed as possible.
The actual dance begins 1:10 in and features some key moments most dances don’t, such as: 
A projected baseball field. CGI dinger that flies right at your face. A slide into 1st despite clearly hitting a home run. Sassy butt bumps. Ross and partner Lindsay Arnold fared pretty well on the night. They scored 28/40, and Ross was praised for his energy on the dance floor. That means we’ll be seeing more David Ross dances — which is a good thing.
